          "answer": "B",
          "rationale": "When source documents may not contain certain information, schema fields should be optional/nullable. Required fields force the model to produce a value even when none exists, leading to fabrication. Making the field nullable explicitly allows the model to return null, signaling that the information was not found. Prompt instructions (A) are less reliable than schema design. Removing the field (D) loses it for documents that do have it."
