          "stem": "You're adding error handling wrappers to external API calls across a 120-file codebase. The task has three phases: (1) discovering all API call locations and patterns, (2) designing the error handling approach collaboratively, and (3) implementing wrappers consistently. During Phase 1, Claude generates verbose output listing hundreds of call sites with context. Your context window is filling rapidly before you've finished discovery.\n\nWhat's the most effective approach to complete this while maintaining implementation consistency?",
